.\" Man page for urpm
.TH URPM 1 "January 2025" "urpm-ng" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
urpm \- modern package manager for Mageia Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B urpm
.RI [ options ]
.I command
.RI [ arguments ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B urpm
is a modern package manager for Mageia Linux, providing fast dependency
resolution using libsolv, P2P package sharing between LAN machines,
and an intuitive command-line interface.
.PP
It is designed as a complete rewrite of the classic urpmi toolset.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version number and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Verbose output.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Quiet output.
.TP
.B \-\-nocolor
Disable colored output.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Package Installation and Removal
.TP
.B i|install \fIpackage\fR ...
Install one or more packages.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-auto
No confirmation prompt.
.TP
.B \-\-download\-only
Download packages without installing.
.TP
.B \-\-without\-recommends
Do not install recommended packages.
.TP
.B \-\-with\-suggests
Also install suggested packages.
.TP
.B \-\-only\-peers
Only download from LAN peers, no upstream mirrors.
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-buildrequires ", " \-\-builddeps ", " \-\-br " " \fI[spec]\fR
Install build dependencies from spec file or SRPM. Auto-detects if no file specified.
.TP
.B \-\-sync
Wait for all scriptlets and triggers to complete before returning.
.TP
.B \-\-allow\-arch " " \fIarch\fR
Allow additional architectures beyond system arch and noarch. Can be repeated.
By default, only packages matching the system architecture (e.g., x86_64) and
noarch are considered. Use this option to install 32-bit packages on 64-bit
systems (e.g., \fB\-\-allow\-arch i686\fR for wine or steam).
.RE
.TP
.B e|erase \fIpackage\fR ...
Remove one or more packages. Aliases: \fBremove\fR.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-auto
No confirmation prompt.
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-orphans
Also remove orphaned dependencies.
.RE
.TP
.B autoremove
Remove orphaned packages, old kernels, failed dependencies, or build dependencies.
Alias: \fBar\fR.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-orphans
Remove orphaned packages (default if no selector given).
.TP
.BR \-k ", " \-\-kernels
Remove old kernels (keeps running + N recent, see \fBurpm config kernel\-keep\fR).
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-faildeps
Remove orphan dependencies from interrupted transactions.
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-buildrequires ", " \-\-builddeps ", " \-\-br
Remove packages installed as build dependencies (tracked in
.IR /var/lib/rpm/installed\-through\-builddeps.list ")."
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
All of the above.
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-auto
No confirmation prompt.
.RE
.SS Metadata and Package Updates
.TP
.B update \fR[\fImedia\fR]
Update media metadata only (apt-style). Does not upgrade packages.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-files
Also sync files.xml for media with sync_files enabled.
.RE
.TP
.B u|upgrade \fR[\fIpackage\fR ...]
Upgrade packages (system upgrade if none specified).
.RS
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-auto
No confirmation prompt.
.TP
.B \-\-with\-recommends
Install recommended packages.
.TP
.B \-\-only\-peers
Only download from LAN peers, no upstream mirrors.
.TP
.B \-\-allow\-arch " " \fIarch\fR
Allow additional architectures (e.g., \fB\-\-allow\-arch i686\fR).
.RE
.SS Package Information
.TP
.B q|query \fIpattern\fR
Search for packages by name or description. Aliases: \fBs\fR, \fBsearch\fR.
.TP
.B show \fIpackage\fR
Show detailed package information.
.TP
.B list \fR[\fIpattern\fR]
List packages. Use \fB\-\-installed\fR for installed packages only.
.TP
.B provides \fIpackage\fR
Show what capabilities a package provides.
.TP
.B whatprovides \fIcapability\fR
Find packages providing a capability.
.TP
.B find \fIpattern\fR
Find which package contains a file matching the pattern.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-installed
Search only in installed packages.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-available
Search only in available packages (requires files.xml sync).
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-limit " " \fIN\fR
Limit results to N matches.
.PP
By default, searches both installed and available packages.
Available package search requires enabling files.xml sync via
\fBurpm media set \-\-all \-\-sync-files\fR followed by
\fBurpm media update \-\-files\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B depends \fIpackage\fR
Show package dependencies.
.TP
.B rdepends \fIpackage\fR
Show reverse dependencies.
.TP
.B why \fIpackage\fR
Explain why a package is installed.
.SS Media and Server Management
.TP
.B media \fR[\fIsubcommand\fR]
Manage media sources. Without subcommand, lists media.
.RS
.TP
.B list
List configured media.
.TP
.B add \fIname\fR \fIurl\fR
Add a new media.
.TP
.B remove \fIname\fR
Remove a media.
.TP
.B enable \fIname\fR
Enable a media.
.TP
.B disable \fIname\fR
Disable a media.
.TP
.B update \fR[\fIname\fR]
Update media metadata (parallel).
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-files
Also sync files.xml for media with sync_files enabled. Required for
\fBurpm find\fR to search available packages.
.RE
.TP
.B import
Import media configuration from urpmi.
.TP
.B link \fIname\fR \fI+server\fR|\fI-server\fR ...
Link or unlink servers to a media. Use +server to add, -server to remove.
Use +all/-all to add/remove all servers. Only links servers that have the media available.
.TP
.B set \fIname\fR \fR[\fIoptions\fR]
Modify media settings.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-shared \fIyes\fR|\fIno\fR
Enable/disable sharing this media with peers.
.TP
.B \-\-replication \fIpolicy\fR
Replication policy: none, on_demand, seed.
.TP
.B \-\-seeds \fIsections\fR
rpmsrate sections for seed replication (comma-separated), e.g., INSTALL,CAT_PLASMA5,CAT_GNOME.
.TP
.B \-\-quota \fIsize\fR
Per-media quota (e.g., 5G, 500M).
.TP
.B \-\-retention \fIdays\fR
Days to keep cached packages.
.TP
.B \-\-priority \fIN\fR
Media priority (higher = preferred).
.TP
.B \-\-sync\-files
Enable automatic files.xml sync for this media. Required for \fBurpm find\fR
to search available packages.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-sync\-files
Disable automatic files.xml sync.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
Apply setting to all enabled media (use with \fB\-\-sync\-files\fR or \fB\-\-no\-sync\-files\fR).
.RE
.TP
.B autoconfig \fB\-\-release\fR \fIversion\fR
Auto-add official Mageia media for a release. Aliases: \fBauto\fR, \fBac\fR.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-release " " \fIversion\fR
Mageia release (e.g., 10, cauldron). Required.
.TP
.B \-\-arch \fIarch\fR
Target architecture (default: host).
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be added without making changes.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-nonfree
Skip nonfree media.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-tainted
Skip tainted media.
.RE
.TP
.B discover \fIurl\fR
Discover all available media from a repository's \fBmedia.cfg\fR file.
Works with official mirrors, community repos (MLO), and corporate mirrors.
Existing servers hosting the same content are automatically linked
(verified by MD5 checksum of synthesis.hdlist.cz).
Aliases: \fBdisc\fR.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be added without making changes.
.TP
.B \-\-enable
Enable all discovered media, including those marked \fBnoauto\fR in media.cfg.
.TP
.B \-\-sources
Include SRPMS media (excluded by default).
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Include debug media (excluded by default).
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B server \fR[\fIsubcommand\fR]
Manage download servers. Without subcommand, lists servers.
.RS
.TP
.B list
.RS
List configured servers.
.sp
.BR \-\-all
Lists all servers showing also those disabled
.RE
.TP
.B add \fIname\fR \fIurl\fR
Add a new server.
.TP
.B remove \fIname\fR [\fIname\fR ...]
Remove one or more servers.
.TP
.B enable \fIname\fR
Enable a server.
.TP
.B disable \fIname\fR
Disable a server.
.TP
.B priority \fIname\fR \fIN\fR
Set server priority (higher number = preferred, default 50).
.TP
.B test \fR[\fIname\fR]
Test connectivity to a server (or all enabled servers) and auto-detect the best
IP mode (auto/ipv4/ipv6/dual).
.TP
.B ip-mode \fIname\fR \fImode\fR
Force the IP version used when connecting to a server.
Valid modes: \fBauto\fR (system default), \fBipv4\fR, \fBipv6\fR, \fBdual\fR
(both work, prefer IPv4).
.TP
.B stats \fIname\fR
Show measured performance statistics for a server: download speed (EWMA of
past downloads), latency, success/failure counts, and last check time.
Statistics are updated automatically after each download and metadata sync.
.TP
.B autoconfig
Auto-discover and add the fastest servers from the Mageia mirror API.
Tests latency to all candidates and keeps the N best.
Saves measured latency so server ordering is meaningful from the first download.
.sp
Geographic filtering (country/continent whitelist or blacklist) is applied
from the
.B [server]
section in
.IR /etc/urpm/conf.d/10\-server.cfg .
Set
.B auto_add = false
to disable all automatic server addition.
.RE
.SS P2P and Cache
.TP
.B peer \fR[\fIsubcommand\fR]
Manage P2P peers. Without subcommand, lists peers.
.RS
.TP
.B list
List discovered peers and download statistics.
.TP
.B blacklist \fIhost\fR
Block a peer.
.TP
.B unblacklist \fIhost\fR
Unblock a peer.
.TP
.B clean \fIhost\fR
Delete RPMs downloaded from a peer.
.RE
.TP
.B cache \fIsubcommand\fR
Manage the package cache.
.RS
.TP
.B clean
Remove orphan RPMs from cache.
.TP
.B info
Show cache statistics.
.RE
.SS History and Rollback
.TP
.B history \fR[\fIN\fR]
Show transaction history. Default: last 10 transactions.
.TP
.B rollback \fIspec\fR
Rollback transactions.
.RS
.TP
.B rollback 5
Rollback last 5 transactions.
.TP
.B rollback to 42
Rollback to transaction #42.
.TP
.B rollback to 26/11/2025
Rollback to a specific date.
.RE
.TP
.B undo \fR[\fIN\fR]
Undo last transaction, or transaction #N.
.SS Configuration
.TP
.B config \fIsubcommand\fR
Manage urpm configuration.
.TP
.B key \fIsubcommand\fR
Manage GPG keys for package verification.
.TP
.B mark \fIpackage\fR manual|auto
Mark packages as manually or automatically installed.
.TP
.B hold \fR[\fIpackage\fR ...] [\fB\-r\fR \fIreason\fR]
Hold packages to prevent upgrades and obsoletes replacement.
Without arguments, lists held packages.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-reason " " \fIreason\fR
Record a reason for the hold.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List held packages.
.RE
.TP
.B unhold \fIpackage\fR ...
Remove hold from packages, allowing them to be upgraded or replaced.
.SS Initialization and Download
.TP
.B init \fR[\fB\-\-release\fR \fIversion\fR] [\fB\-\-mirrorlist\fR \fIurl\fR]
Initialize urpm with standard Mageia media. Tests mirrors and configures the best ones.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-release " " \fIversion\fR
Mageia version (e.g., 10, cauldron).
.TP
.B \-\-urpm\-root " " \fIpath\fR
Initialize in a chroot directory.
.RE
.TP
.B download \fIpackage\fR ...
Download packages to cache without installing.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-release " " \fIversion\fR
Target release for cross-release downloads.
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-buildrequires ", " \-\-builddeps ", " \-\-br " " \fI[spec]\fR
Download build dependencies from spec file.
.TP
.B \-\-only\-peers
Only download from LAN peers, no upstream mirrors.
.TP
.B \-\-allow\-arch " " \fIarch\fR
Allow additional architectures (e.g., \fB\-\-allow\-arch i686\fR).
.RE
.SS Container Build System
.TP
.B image \fR[\fIsubcommand\fR]
Manage container images. Without subcommand, lists images.
Aliases: \fBimg\fR.
.RS
.TP
.B make \fB\-\-release\fR \fIversion\fR \fB\-\-tag\fR \fItag\fR [\fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR]
Create a minimal Docker/Podman image for RPM builds.
Aliases: \fBm\fR.
The top-level command \fBmkimage\fR is a deprecated alias for \fBimage make\fR.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-release " " \fIversion\fR
Mageia version (e.g., 10, cauldron).
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-tag " " \fItag\fR
Image tag (e.g., mageia:10-build).
.TP
.B \-\-profile " " \fIname\fR
Package profile (default: build). Available profiles: build (RPM build environment),
ci (CI/testing), minimal (minimal system with urpm). Profiles are loaded from
/usr/share/urpm/profiles/*.yaml and /etc/urpm/profiles/*.yaml.
.TP
.B \-\-arch " " \fIarch\fR
Target architecture (default: host).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-packages " " \fIlist\fR
Additional packages (comma-separated).
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-buildrequires " " \fIspec_or_srpm\fR
Pre-install BuildRequires from a .spec or .src.rpm file into the image.
.TP
.B \-\-runtime " " docker|podman
Container runtime (default: auto-detect).
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-chroot
Keep temporary chroot after image creation.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-workdir " " \fIpath\fR
Working directory for chroot (default: /tmp).
.RE
.TP
.B update \fItag\fR [\fB\-\-runtime\fR \fIruntime\fR]
Update an existing image in-place (sync media and upgrade packages).
Aliases: \fBu\fR.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-runtime " " docker|podman
Container runtime (default: auto-detect).
.RE
.TP
.B list \fR[\fB\-\-runtime\fR \fIruntime\fR]
List container images.
Aliases: \fBl\fR, \fBls\fR.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-runtime " " docker|podman
Container runtime (default: auto-detect).
.RE
.TP
.B delete \fItags\fR ... [\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-\-runtime\fR \fIruntime\fR]
Delete one or more container images.
Aliases: \fBd\fR, \fBrm\fR.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Force deletion without confirmation.
.TP
.B \-\-runtime " " docker|podman
Container runtime (default: auto-detect).
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B build \fB\-\-image\fR \fItag\fR \fIsource\fR ...
Build RPM packages in isolated containers. Media metadata and installed packages
inside the container are automatically updated before building.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-image " " \fItag\fR
Docker/Podman image to use.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIdir\fR
Output directory for SRPM builds (default: ./build-output).
For .spec files, results go to workspace/RPMS/ and workspace/SRPMS/.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-with\-rpms " " \fIpattern\fR
Pre-install local RPMs in container before build. Useful when building
a package that depends on a library you just built locally. Supports glob
patterns and can be repeated. Example: \fB-w 'RPMS/x86_64/libfoo*.rpm'\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-update
Skip media sync and package update before building.
.TP
.B \-\-runtime " " docker|podman
Container runtime (default: auto-detect).
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-parallel " " \fIN\fR
Number of parallel builds (default: 1).
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-container
Keep container after build (for debugging).
.PP
Sources can be .src.rpm files or .spec files. For .spec files, sources are
automatically copied from the SOURCES/ directory (supports workspace/SPECS/
and workspace/SOURCES/ layouts).
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/urpm/
Database and cache directory.
.TP
.I /var/lib/urpm/packages.db
SQLite database for package metadata and history.
.TP
.I /var/lib/urpm/medias/
Downloaded packages cache.
.TP
.I /etc/urpm/urpm.cfg
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/urpm/conf.d/*.cfg
Drop-in configuration overrides (loaded alphabetically after urpm.cfg).
The
.B [server]
section in
.I 10\-server.cfg
controls automatic mirror addition and geographic filtering
(country_blacklist, country_whitelist, continent_blacklist, continent_whitelist, auto_add).
.TP
.I /etc/bash_completion.d/urpm
Bash completion script.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Install a package:
.B urpm i firefox
.TP
Search for packages:
.B urpm q video player
.TP
Update all packages:
.B urpm u
.TP
Remove a package without asking for confirmation :
.B urpm e \-y gimp
.TP
Show why a package is installed:
.B urpm why libpng
.TP
Update media metadata:
.B urpm m u
